Note the two options we pass to <code>session.run()</code>:

- <code>mean_pool</code>: The first option sets <code>pooling</code> to <code>mean</code>. Pooling referes to how token-level embedding representations are compressed into a single sentence embedding that reflects the meaning of the entire sentence. Average pooling is the most common type of pooling for sentence embeddings.
- <code>normalize</code>: The second option tells to normalize the embedding vector so that it can be used with distance measures like dot product. A normalized vector means its length (magnitude) is 1 - also referred to as a unit vector. A vector is normalized by dividing each element by the vector's length (magnitude), which maintains its direction but changes its length to 1.

